cyclone.name: ARTHUR
cyclone.current_location: about 210 miles SSW of Cape Hatteras, North Carolina
cyclone.trajectory: tracking north-northeast near the Outer Banks, then accelerating northeast and east over the western Atlantic
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or just east of the Outer Banks, NC

weather_observation.watch_coast: None in Florida; Tropical Storm Warning only from Surf City to Duck NC and adjacent sounds
weather_observation.warning_coast: Surf City to Duck NC including Pamlico and Albemarle Sounds
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Georgia and South Carolina offshore waters, North Carolina coast (especially Outer Banks), and portions of the mid-Atlantic offshore waters
weather_observation.wind: Breezy onshore flow; tropical-storm-force winds not expected at Port Canaveral
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor surf and elevated seas possible but no significant surge inundation expected
weather_observation.rainfall: Outer rainbands could bring less than 1 inch of rainfall
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous rip currents and rough surf along the east-central Florida beaches
